ERRORS:

Compiler error

syntax error or semantic error
syntax errors rise due to lack of following of cpp rules while the semantic error rise due to the
lack of the logic of the code

Compiler Warnings:
Don't ignore compiler warnings

Linker errors
Linker errors rise due to linker is trying to put all the pieces of the program together but some piece is
missing. This can happen due to syntax errors, semantic error or missing libraries

for example: undefined reference to x or something is an example of a linker error

Runtime errors:

It happens when the program is executing and are hard to predict sometimes

Logic errors:

Logic errors rise due to bugs in the code due to mistakes in logic made by the programmer.
Incorrect handling of if-else statements is a classic example of a Logic error
